    <h2 id="golden-rules">10 Golden Safety Rules for Chatting With Strangers</h2>
    <p>Follow these 10 rules every single time you chat with strangers online and you will have a safe experience:</p>

    <ol class="blg-steps">
      <li><strong>Never share your real name</strong> — Use a nickname or username instead of your actual name</li>
      <li><strong>Never share your location</strong> — Do not tell strangers your city, neighbourhood, school, or workplace</li>
      <li><strong>Never share your phone number</strong> — This can be used to find your identity and location</li>
      <li><strong>Use the block button freely</strong> — If anyone makes you uncomfortable even slightly, block them immediately</li>
      <li><strong>Never click links from strangers</strong> — Links can lead to phishing sites, malware, or scams</li>
      <li><strong>Do not turn on your camera too fast</strong> — Wait until you feel comfortable before showing your face</li>
      <li><strong>Never agree to meet in person</strong> — No matter how nice someone seems, meeting strangers is dangerous</li>
      <li><strong>Trust your gut feeling</strong> — If something feels wrong, it probably is — leave immediately</li>
      <li><strong>Use moderated platforms only</strong> — Choose sites with AI moderation and active reporting systems</li>
      <li><strong>Tell someone you trust</strong> — Let a friend or family member know you use random chat platforms</li>
    </ol>

